sql:
SELECT username
FROM users
WHERE user_id = (SELECT user_id FROM images WHERE title = 'Baby Yoda');

external_knowledge:
- "digital voyagers" refers to users who upload images;
- "footprint of the search engine giant" metaphorically refers to the word "google";
- The "works" mentioned here are the images uploaded by users.

sql:
SELECT title 
FROM images 
WHERE id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- "Shining stars in the gallery of knowledge" metaphorically refers to popular images; 
- "Radiating the most light" metaphorically means having the highest combined score of likes, comments, and views;
- "The past month" refers to the last 30 days.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT user_id
FROM images
WHERE privacy_setting = 'private';

SELECT title, url, total_likes
FROM images
WHERE user_id = 1 AND total_likes = (SELECT MAX(total_likes) FROM images WHERE user_id = 1);

SELECT DISTINCT users.user_id, users.username
FROM users
JOIN images ON users.user_id = images.user_id;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS total_unique_voices
FROM (
  SELECT user_id FROM images
  UNION
  SELECT user_id FROM image_comments
) AS combined_users;

SELECT title
FROM images
WHERE total_likes > (SELECT AVG(total_likes) FROM images);

external_knowledge:
- 'Popular' in this context refers to images with more than 10 likes;
- 'Web-friendly slugs' refer to the SEO-friendly URL segments;
- 'Creators' refer to the users who uploaded the images.

- "names" refers to 'title' of the images; 
- "identities of the creators" refers to 'username' of the users; 
- "collection of visual pieces" refers to the image entries in the database;
- "from the oldest to the newest" means ordered by the time of creation, from earliest to latest.

sql:
SELECT image_id, action
FROM image_upload_history
WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM image_upload_history 
WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(image_views.image_id)
FROM image_views
JOIN likes ON image_views.user_id = likes.user_id AND image_views.image_id = likes.image_id;

SELECT title, url, total_likes, comments_count
FROM images
WHERE user_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'Stars of the digital cosmos' refers to images;
- 'Celestial content creators' refers to users with the role 'content creator';
- 'Shone the brightest with the most hearts' indicates images with the highest number of active likes;
- 'Visible to all' means the images have a privacy setting of 'public';
- 'Celestial gallery' is a metaphor for the image database.
